stylometry: In our group project we were trying to figure out how many cooks and/or servers were needed during a certain night of the week to lower labor costs.  To do this we needed to know our arrival rates, how much are wages are, how much guests were spending, and how many guests each server was responsible for during a certain time frame.  So we decided after looking at our server utilization rate that it was most efficient to have no more than three servers on, on a Tuesday morning while having an average arrival rate of 37 something.  Meaning all three servers could give satisfactory service for the number amount of guest they were waiting on.  By doing this we cut labor costs by 50% and had a server utilization rate of something like 48% which was much highe than in the beginng when we had 8 servers with a utilization rate of something like 0.5%
